      <guid>/wiaposts/understanding-maya/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;/assets/images/wiapost/5082-Understanding-Maya.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Understanding Maya&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Understanding Maya 
    &lt;div id=&#34;understanding-maya&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#understanding-maya&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you live near a river or ocean  &lt;br&gt;
then water is everything for you.  &lt;br&gt;
Rain, ice, food, plant all have their source in water.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you live near the north or the south pole of the earth  &lt;br&gt;
then ice is everything for you.  &lt;br&gt;
Everything is made of ice.  &lt;br&gt;
Water, vapor, cloud, life around all have sources in ice.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
